h1. Disributed Method Invocation (DMI) Example
h2. Summary
This example shows how to use Distributed Method Invocation with Terracotta. DMI is a good choice to use if you want to broadcast a message to many clients.
h2. How to run
*Node 1:* {code} $ javac *.java $ start-tc-server & $ dso-java Main Waiting for dmi method calls... {code}
*Node 2:* {code} $ dso-java Main rec Waiting for dmi method calls... {code}
*Node 3:* {code} $ dso-java Main Enter a message> hello hello {code}
On nodes 1 & 2 you will also see: {code} $ dso-java Main rec Waiting for dmi method calls... hello {code}
